post_text:
Beginning Monday, September 14th, 2020 ALL enrolled students(including online learners) will receive free reimbursable breakfast and lunch meals each day school is in session. Although the regular school meals will be free of charge there will still be a charge for al a carte items. Additionally, there will continue to be a charge of adult meals. The USDA has approved the program to operate through Decmeber 31, 2020 or until the funds run out. This approval is not retroactive. Meals served from August 31st-Sept 11th have been charged to accounts. Only reimbursable meals including all required nutritional components are covered. Not included are a la carte items, snack milk and any other "extra" purchases outside of a meal. One breakfast and one lunch per day per student is included.
Online learners-if you did not request meals you will still NOT receive them unless you contact the mail office.

Thank you for your continued support of the Nutrition Program as we navigate through these unprecedented times.

The Starmont-West Central varsity girl's team won the meet last night, placing individually in 6 of the top 7 spots. WC's Annika Kent-Thomas finished 7th overall.

post_text:
After careful consideration and discussions with administrative groups, West Central will be allowing the use of gaiters. This of course will be continued with reviews of policies during this unprecedented period of time.

West Central still highly recommends the use of facial masks that have two or more layers of washable, breathable fabric which completely covers your mouth and nose and fit snugly against the side of the face with no gaps.

https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/prevent-getting-sick/about-face-coverings.html

Dress code will still follow the school appropriate guidelines for both gaiters and standard masks. Designs should reflect the decorum of the school day.

post_text:
Hello everyone!

My name is Samantha Baumgartner and I am the new PK-12 At-Risk Coordinator and Activities Director. I come to West Central with a mental health and behavioral health background. I previously worked as a School Counselor at MFL MarMac and prior to that I worked as a Behavioral Health Intervention Specialist with Families First. I completed my Master's degree at Buena Vista University in PK-12 School Counseling and completed my Bachelor's degree at UNI in Family Studies with minors in Mental Health and Psychology as well as some coursework and field experience in elementary education. I live in Elkader with my husband, Devon, and our two dogs named Bodhi and Belle. I enjoy hiking, kayaking, reading, and gardening. I look forward to building relationships with the wonderful Blue Devil community!

post_text: My name is Denise Menne. I will be the new second grader teacher at WC this year. I live with my husband and two boys on an acreage outside of West Union. My oldest son, Ian, graduated from NFV in May and our youngest is a sophomore at NFV. My husband is a carpenter. I am a UIU graduate, earning my BA in 1996 then going back later to get my teaching certification. I have worked with children and families for many years and taught 4-5-6th grades at Sacred Heart in Oelwein. I love to spend time with my family. I love history, reading, and DIY. My husband and I love to hike and be outdoors. I am looking forward to my new adventure at West Central.

post_text:
Hello everyone!!
My name is Jamie Vargason and I will be teaching k12 Art!! I was raised and currently live in Westgate now with my three children (Jordynn 13, Myree 7, Alice 5). As a 2008 West Central graduate, I am so excited to be back to teach in my home community. After high school, I studied art education at Upper Iowa University and worked in Oelwein and Sumner as a special ed paraeducator. I can't wait to explore and teach art with students to help not only with their artistic talent but to create friendship bonds, emotion, and challenge students to never give up no matter what they are doing. I love camping, hiking, fishing (anything outdoors), playing marbles, of course creating artwork, and most of all hanging with my family.

post_text: My name is Ashten Wolff. I teach Special Education for students in 4th, 5th, and 6th grade. I graduated from Upper Iowa University in 2018 with my Bachelor's degree in Elementary Education. Currently I am pursuing my Master's of Education in Special Education at Upper Iowa University. After graduation, I joined the Peace Corps and taught English in the Philippines. I lived in the Philippines for over a year. After the Peace Corps, I taught 2nd grade as a long term substitute at East Buchanan. One of my favorite things to do is bake! During the first part of the COVID-19 pandemic, I baked lots of sourdough bread and cakes. I also love to read! My favorite genre of books is historical fiction! I am excited to be a part of the West Central community! Go Blue Devils!

post_text:
One of the special things about West Central is the honoring of the 50-year graduates during graduation. Since we won't be able to do that this Spring, we thought it might be nice to celebrate them by sharing their senior pictures from the 1970 Blue Shadows. The class motto was "Search for wisdom, for with it comes understanding."

We encourage you to tag family and friends in the comments. Hopefully, we'll be able to get the class together in the fall and honor them at Homecoming.

The 2020 graduation alternative ceremony is scheduled for June 5 at 7 pm. Activities will be held outside the main entrance. Go Blue Devils!!

post_text: Dear West Central Juniors and Seniors, On Wednesday, May 20, 2020 the West Central administration has decided to cancel prom for the 2019-2020 school year: To protect the public's health and wellbeing, the state of Iowa is reopening slowly and at this time it is still recommending smaller gatherings held in enclosed spaces that do not allow social distancing also be postponed or canceled or held virtually. With this continued recommended information from health providers, I regret to inform you that this years Junior/Senior Prom is cancelled. This decision was not made lightly and I sincerely hope that students and families understand that this is in the best interest of students' health . Sincerely, Matthew Molumby, Principal

post_text: UPDATE TO EMAIL ADDRESS: The WC Board will be grilling again this year, only this time it will be a drive through service! If you would like to take part in the feast, please contact the school by phone or email at wclunch@gmail.com. Please provide your name, number of people and your protein selection (Hamburger or Hotdog). We would like to have orders placed by May 12. Join us at the school, from the comfort of your car! Meal to be handed out to the community 5:00pm-7:00pm, May 22nd. Thank you and take care!

post_text: MAYNARD, WESTGATE & RANDALIA RESIDENTS: Let's host a "Bear Hunt" for our West Central students. Put a stuffed animal in your window (porch, fence, tree, etc) by Wednesday night, March 25 at 6:00. WEST CENTRAL PARENTS: Pack your kids in the car, with a sack supper if you like, and drive around these communities looking for the bears! It's supposed to be somewhat warm so, residents, feel free to sit out on your yard, deck or driveway and wave to the kids!

post_text:
With permission from Erhart, this post was copied from his son Karl's Facebook page. Congratulations to Erhart for receiving this distinguished service award!

"Last night was quite a memorable one. I had the honor to attend the IFCA Awards banquet and see an number of great men honored for their careers devoted to helping kids. However, the best one I got to see was my dad (Erhart) receiving a distinguished service award for his many years of driving school bus for West Central. He started driving bus in 1964 as a senior in high school. I am so proud of my father and his dedication to his kids at West Central. Thank you to Steve Milder for nominating him. I know Mom was watching too. One of the best parts of the night was Dad getting to shake hands with the College Football coaches. (Campbell/Ferentz/Farley). I asked if he knew them and he said "I've seen them on TV". I'm told we will get some professional photos soon. Mine aren't the best."

post_text:
The Upper Iowa Basketball teams would like to invite all students (Pre-K through High School) and other local youth to attend YOUTH DAY on Saturday, February 1 as they take on the University of Minnesota Duluth! The women’s basketball game is scheduled to tipoff at 3:30 p.m. in Dorman Gymnasium with the men’s basketball game to follow at approximately 5:30 p.m. ALL YOUTH WILL RECEIVE FREE ADMITTANCE INTO THE BASKETBALL GAMES ! (If under 12 years old, must be accompanied by a paying adult)

There will also be Meet & Greet/Autograph opportunities with players and coaches from the UIU Men’s & Women’s Basketball teams that afternoon. The men's team will be available in the Dorman Gym Lobby for a meet-and-greet during the second quarter of the women's game. The women’s team will be available in the lobby approximately 20 minutes after the conclusion of the WBB game.

Help us pack the stands and support UIU Peacock Basketball as they take on the Minnesota Duluth Bulldogs!

Dennis Soppe of the National Executive Committee of the American Legion presents West Central's Cameron Rohde with a certificate from the Department of the Iowa American Legion High School Oratorical Scholarship Program "A Constitutional Speech Contest". Cameron has advanced through two previous competitions and will now advance to the next level on January 26 at Tama Hall on the Hawkeye Community College Campus. Cameron is supported by the Maynard American Legion and has been named an Honorary Member.
Cameron is also with the Oelwein Legion as Sons of the American Legion. Cameron's father and grandfather, along with many other family members, are veterans of military service.

shared_text:
West Central Community Schools added 43 new photos.
January 13 at 8:43 AM ·

This past weekend West Central hosted a 4-6th Grade Boys and Girls Basketball tournament. It was awesome seeing the school packed with people and all of our young players out on their home court enjoying some competitive basketball. Huge Shout out to all the people who were involved in putting together the Little Blue Devil basketball tournament. We hosted 20 games and over 80 volunteer spots were filled by Junior High, JV & Varsity basketball players, coaches, parents, and community members. Thank you to the West Central Booster Club along with the Jr Post Prom committee in providing phenomenal food selections for the spectators that attended the day’s events. Last and most importantly, we’d like to thank the volunteer coaches who share their time, talent and their enthusiasm, developing these young athletics as they transition into Jr High School Basketball. We are so very proud of these kids and the wonderful talent they will be bringing to the WC basketball court here in the next couple years. Good luck to everyone on the remainder of your tournament season!!
